---
<section class="reviews" id="reviews">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section__title" data-i18n="reviews.title">What people who passed are saying</h2>
    <p class="section__subtitle" data-i18n="reviews.subtitle">They started exactly where you are now.</p>
    <div class="reviews__featured">
      <div class="reviews__featured-photo">
        <img src="/pics/license-success.jpg" alt="A newly licensed Florida real estate agent holding her license outside the DBPR Division of Real Estate office" loading="lazy" width="1100" height="825" />
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__featured-body">
        <div class="reviews__featured-badge"><span class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</span> Success story</div>
        <h3 class="reviews__featured-title">This is what passing looks&nbsp;like</h3>
        <p class="reviews__featured-text">A brand-new Florida real estate license, straight from the DBPR. Hundreds of legal terms, an exam in English, a language that wasn't her first. She walked out licensed. <strong>You're next.</strong></p>
        <div class="reviews__featured-meta">
          <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4"></path><path d="M21 12c0 4.97-4.03 9-9 9s-9-4.03-9-9 4.03-9 9-9c1.5 0 2.91.37 4.15 1.02"></path></svg>
          <span>Florida &middot; Department of Business &amp; Professional Regulation</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="reviews__grid">
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card1.text">I failed the test twice. The ideas were not the problem, the English words were. Once every question had a translation next to it, it all made sense. I passed.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>Carmen R.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source" data-i18n="reviews.card1.source">Spanish</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card2.text">I was afraid I would never remember hundreds of terms. My saved words came back to me just before I forgot them. On exam day I remembered them all.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>Dmitry K.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source">Русский</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card3.text">The legal terms in English were too hard for me. With the audio and the translation together, you hear it and understand it right away. The material stopped being scary.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>Mei L.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source" data-i18n="reviews.card3.source">Chinese</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card4.text">In other apps the answers were only in English, and I understood about half. Here the reason is shown line by line with a translation. You learn why, instead of just memorizing the right letter.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>João P.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source" data-i18n="reviews.card4.source">Portuguese</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card5.text">Between work and family, I had almost no time to study. I listened to questions on my way to work and at the gym, and the hours added up on their own. I passed.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>Aisha M.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source" data-i18n="reviews.card5.source">Arabic</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews__card">
        <div class="reviews__stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
        <p class="reviews__text" data-i18n="reviews.card6.text">I did not know where to start. There was so much to learn, and it scared me. The app found my weak spots and told me what to study next. I passed on my first try.</p>
        <div class="reviews__author">
          <strong>Sofia V.</strong>
          <span class="reviews__source" data-i18n="reviews.card6.source">Spanish</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
